Aim

To write a Python program to perform various list operations such as append, insert, remove, pop, sorting, and finding sum, maximum, and minimum values in a list.

Algorithm
Start the program.
Create a list my_list with elements [3, 1, 4, 1, 5].
Print the original list.
Use the append() function to add the element 9 at the end of the list.
Print the updated list.
Use the insert() function to insert the element 7 at index position 2.
Print the updated list.
Use the remove() function to remove the first occurrence of element 1 from the list.
Print the updated list.
Use the pop() function to remove the last element from the list and display it
Use the sorted() function to display the list in sorted order.
Use sum() to calculate the sum of all elements in the list.
Use max() to find the largest element in the list.
Use min() to find the smallest element in the list.
Stop the program.

EXECUTE
my_list = [3, 1, 4, 1, 5]

print("Original:", my_list)
my_list.append(9)
print("After append:", my_list)
my_list.insert(2, 7)
print("After insert:", my_list)
my_list.remove(1)
print("After remove:", my_list)
print("Pop:", my_list.pop())
print("Sorted:", sorted(my_list))
print("Sum:", sum(my_list))
print("Max:", max(my_list))
print("Min:", min(my_list))

OUTPUT
Original: [3, 1, 4, 1, 5]
After append: [3, 1, 4, 1, 5, 9]
After insert: [3, 1, 7, 4, 1, 5, 9]
After remove: [3, 7, 4, 1, 5, 9]
Pop: 9
Sorted: [1, 3, 4, 5, 7]
Sum: 20
Max: 7
Min: 1
